main event: A civilian observer reported seeing a round, star-like object that changed color from silver to reddish orange over Chesapeake, Virginia on May 3, 1965.
interesting points: The object appeared to move downward and to the west very slowly for about 30 degrees, then reversed its course until it passed from view.
The object was visible for about 4 minutes.
Binoculars were used to observe the object.
The sighting occurred within a known Navy warning area.
The report concludes that the object was likely related to activities in the area at the time.
sighted object: A round, star-like object that changed color from silver to reddish orange
photographs: No photographs were included in the report
